article.headline: Youngstown State 70, Lock Haven 56
article.story: YOUNGSTOWN, Ohio (AP) -- Brian Radakovich and Quin Humphrey scored 16 points apiece to help Youngstown State beat Lock Haven 70-56 on Sunday in the season opener for the Penguins. John Barber added 13 points and 10 rebounds for Youngstown State, which forced 25 turnovers. Lock Haven's James Chappell had 14 points and Quentin Terry grabbed 13 rebounds. The Bald Eagles (0-2) shot 39 percent from the field. Lock Haven got off to a strong start, grabbing a 30-20 first-half lead on a 3-pointer from Julien Grandgirard. James Chappell and Grandgirard each hit two 3s in the first half. But the Penguins closed out the half with an 11-2 run to pull within one at the break. Youngstown State surged in front in the second half. A layup from John Barber finished off a 10-2 run that made it 50-40 Penguins with 11:50 remaining. Joe Walker had 13 points and eight rebounds and Eddie Christiano finished with 12 points for Lock Haven. Youngstown State's Derrick Harris pitched in nine points off the bench.
